{"type":"message","id":"9e4e5ae7","parentId":"28c0cf27","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:13:14.232Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"41\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"sender\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-25 12:13 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Hi-K (1677157143)\",\n  \"id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"name\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"username\": \"lioptae\"\n}\n```\n\n\"Please use these details to create the draft_facebook_post skill:\n\nUser Input: I will specify the business name (Hi-K or Myan-Poh) and a brief topic (e.g., 'New skincare arrival' or 'Fast shipping to Yangon').\n\nBusiness Context: Use the specific data I trained you on for each brand. If I say 'Hi-K', use the cosmetic/reselling data. If 'Myan-Poh', use the cargo/logistics data.\n\nOutput Format: I want a complete Facebook post including:\n\nEngaging Caption (in Burmese)\n\nCall to Action (CTA)\n\nRelevant Hashtags\n\nImage Prompt Detail: Provide a highly detailed English prompt for DALL-E. It should describe the lighting, style (professional/minimalist), and key elements (e.g., a delivery box for Myan-Poh or a aesthetic cosmetic flat-lay for Hi-K).\n\nDALL-E Integration: That is fine. Generate the prompt for me first. If you have a tool/plugin to call DALL-E, please use it. Otherwise, showing the prompt and the text for my review is the priority.\n\nAdditional Workflow:\nAfter generating both, send them to me via Telegram. I will reply with 'Approve'. Once approved, ask me for the 'Schedule Time'. After I provide the time, you must confirm and prepare to post.\""}],"timestamp":1774440794229}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cd5be22","parentId":"9e4e5ae7","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:13:20.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing New Skill**\n\nI am currently refining the `draft_facebook_post` skill. My focus is on ensuring it accurately captures user input for business name and topic, and then leverages specific training data tailored to each business.\n\n**Creating New Skill**\n\nI am now focused on defining the `draft_facebook_post` skill structure using the `skill-creator` tool, ensuring it can effectively capture business specifics and generate tailored content.\n\n**Defining Skill Structure**\n\nI am currently working on defining the `draft_facebook_post` skill structure using the `skill-creator` tool. My immediate focus is on mapping out how the skill will capture business specifics, such as name and topic, and then process them for tailored content generation.\n\n**Creating New Skill Functionality**\n\nI am now focused on defining the `draft_facebook_post` skill structure using the `skill-creator` tool. My immediate task is to map out how it will capture business specifics and topic, generate tailored Burmese content and DALL-E prompts, and then implement the approval and scheduling workflow.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Okay, I understand. You want to create a new skill called `draft_facebook_post`. This skill will take a business name (Hi-K or Myan-Poh) and a topic from the user, then generate:\n\n1.  A complete Facebook post in Burmese, including an engaging caption, a clear Call to Action (CTA), and relevant hashtags.\n2.  A highly detailed English prompt for DALL-E, tailored to the business and topic, describing lighting, style, and key elements.\n\nThe skill will then present these outputs for your review, and you'll confirm them. After approval, it will prompt you for a schedule time and confirm the posting preparation.\n\nThis is a perfect use case for the `skill-creator` skill. I will use it to define and build the `draft_facebook_post` skill based on your requirements.\n\nFirst, I need to understand how to structure the new skill's definition. The `skill-creator` usually works by taking a detailed blueprint.\n\nCould you please specify (if not already covered) what the exact commands or interaction flow would look like for *using* this new `draft_facebook_post` skill once it's created? For example, how would you invoke it and provide the input?\n\nKnowing this will help me define the skill correctly. Once I have that, I can proceed with using the `skill-creator` tool."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":21157,"output":1934,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23091,"cost":{"input":-21157,"output":-1934,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-23091}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774440794231}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd6d9a40","parentId":"6cd5be22","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:14:38.110Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"43\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"sender\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-25 12:14 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Hi-K (1677157143)\",\n  \"id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"name\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"username\": \"lioptae\"\n}\n```\n\n\"Here is the interaction flow and command structure for the draft_facebook_post skill:\n\n1. Invocation Command:\nI will start by saying:\nDraft a Facebook post for [Business Name] about [Topic/Campaign].\n(e.g., \"Draft a Facebook post for Myan-Poh about our 3-day express delivery to Yangon.\")\n\n2. Generation & Review Phase:\n\nYou will process the request using the trained business data.\n\nYou will reply with:\n\nPost Caption: (Burmese text + CTA + Hashtags)\n\nImage Prompt: (Detailed English prompt for DALL-E)\n\nVisual: (If you can call DALL-E, show the image. If not, show the prompt for my manual use).\n\nThen, ask me: \"Does this look good? Please reply with 'Approve' or provide feedback to edit.\"\n\n3. Approval & Scheduling Phase:\n\nOnce I reply with \"Approve\", you should ask: \"Great! When should I schedule this post? (e.g., Tomorrow at 10 AM)\"\n\nI will provide the time.\n\nYou will then reply with: \"Confirmed. I have scheduled the [Business Name] post for [Parsed Time].\"\n\n4. Execution:\n\nAt the scheduled time, the skill should trigger the final posting action to Facebook (or notify me if the API is not yet linked).\n\nPlease proceed with the skill-creator using this flow.\""}],"timestamp":1774440878107}}
