{"type":"message","id":"bedf0ccf","parentId":"bced6ded","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:15:42.655Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Proposing alternatives for ACP session**\n\nI attempted to spawn an ACP session, but there were errors. I think we should respond with the current status and suggest alternatives. One option is to create a non-thread session or move forward with a manual blueprint. I can draft the skill specification in text, and you can implement it. We could also continue with a threadless session or simulate the flow. I’ll aim to summarize the blueprint concisely.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I tried to spin up the ACP session for draft_facebook_post, but I hit two blockers:\n\n- ACP thread mode is not available because no channel plugin is registered for subagent spawning hooks.\n- A thread-bound session isn’t possible without that plugin, so I can’t create a persistent sub-agent in this environment right now.\n\nWhat I can do next:\n\nOption A — Standalone blueprint you can implement\n- I’ll give you a complete, copy-paste-ready blueprint for the draft_facebook_post skill (data structures, flow steps, prompts, and sample messages). You can implement this in your ACP environment or any agent framework you use.\n\nOption B — Simulated flow here (no ACP session persistence)\n- I’ll outline the entire interaction flow and provide ready-to-use prompts and templates for:\n  - Input parsing (Hi-K or Myan-Poh, topic)\n  - Burmese Facebook post generation (caption, CTA, hashtags)\n  - Detailed English image prompt for DALL-E\n  - Telegram/Inbox review prompts and approval loop\n  - Scheduling prompt and confirmation phrasing\n  - Post execution trigger (API call or notification)\n\nOption C — Alternative runtime (non-ACP)\n- I can adapt the blueprint to a non-ACP script you run locally (e.g., a small CLI or a webhook-based bot) that handles the same flow without ACP.\n\nIf you prefer, I can proceed with Option A (complete blueprint) and you can deploy it locally or in your environment once the ACP/thread plugin is available. Let me know which option you want, and I’ll provide the precise artifacts.\n\nFor reference, here is a compact, implementable blueprint draft you can paste into your system as a starting point (text representation of the skill):\n\n- Name: draft_facebook_post\n- Trigger: “Draft a Facebook post for [Business Name] about [Topic/Campaign].”\n- Context mapping:\n  - If Business Name == Hi-K → use Hi-K cosmetics/reselling data\n  - If Business Name == Myan-Poh → use Myan-Poh cargo/logistics data\n- Generation step:\n  - Output 1: Post Caption (Burmese) with Headline/Body/CTA/Hashtags\n  - Output 2: Image Prompt Detail (Detailed English prompt for DALL-E)\n  - Output 3: Visual (if DALL-E accessible) or the prompt text for manual use\n- Review loop:\n  - Deliver Post Caption, Image Prompt, and Visual to user via Telegram\n  - Prompt: “Does this look good? Please reply with 'Approve' or provide feedback to edit.”\n- Approval step:\n  - On “Approve”: ask “Great! When should I schedule this post? (e.g., Tomorrow at 10 AM)”\n  - Parse the time and schedule a notification or API call to Facebook\n- Execution:\n  - At scheduled time: perform post to Facebook or notify user if API unavailable\n- Data artifacts:\n  - Post caption text ( Burmese )\n  - Image prompt (English)\n  - Optional: image URL or local path after generation\n\nIf you want me to proceed with any of these options, say which one (A, B, or C), and I’ll tailor the deliverables accordingly."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":337,"output":808,"cacheRead":22784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23929,"cost":{"input":-337,"output":-808,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-1145}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774440935441}}
{"type":"message","id":"38bfaf44","parentId":"bedf0ccf","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:16:18.315Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"47\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"sender\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-25 12:16 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Hi-K (1677157143)\",\n  \"id\": \"1677157143\",\n  \"name\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"username\": \"lioptae\"\n}\n```\n\n\"I choose Option C. Please provide the complete Python script and the instructions to run it locally on my Ubuntu server.\n\nThe script should include:\n\nData Integration: How to load my Myan-Poh and Hi-K business data (JSON or Text files).\n\nContent Logic: The logic to generate Burmese captions and English DALL-E prompts using OpenAI API.\n\nTelegram Integration: Use my Telegram Bot token to send the drafts for my approval.\n\nApproval Loop: A simple way for me to reply 'Approve' and set a schedule time.\n\nScheduler: A basic background scheduler (like apscheduler or cron) to handle the final post/notification.\n\nPlease provide the code blueprint and the list of required Python libraries.\""}],"timestamp":1774440978312}}
{"type":"message","id":"19e69607","parentId":"38bfaf44","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:16:37.771Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Developing Script Logic**\n\nI'm currently focusing on structuring the Python script for the `draft_facebook_post` skill. My immediate goal is to establish a robust data loading mechanism for the business context of Hi-K and Myan-Poh, ensuring efficient retrieval. Following that, I'll integrate the OpenAI API for generating Burmese captions, a critical step in this phase.\n\n**Structuring the Core Script**\n\nMy current focus is on the foundational elements for the `draft_facebook_post` skill's standalone Python script. I'm designing the data loading mechanism, anticipating the need to efficiently pull business context for both Hi-K and Myan-Poh, which will then inform the OpenAI API calls for generating Burmese captions and DALL-E prompts.\n\n**Designing Data Loading**\n\nI am currently focused on designing the data loading component of the standalone Python script. My aim is to create efficient functions for reading business context from JSON files specific to Hi-K and Myan-Poh, which will then fuel the subsequent content generation stages.\n\n**Loading Business Context**\n\nI am refining the data loading functions within the Python script. My current effort focuses on efficiently retrieving the specific business context for Hi-K and Myan-Poh from their respective JSON files, which will then be integrated into the prompt generation process for generating Burmese captions.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"User, I understand you need a comprehensive Python script blueprint for the `draft_facebook_post` skill, along with instructions to run it locally on your Ubuntu server. This script will integrate data loading, content generation via OpenAI, Telegram for interaction, and scheduling.\n\nSince I cannot directly create or manage files, execute shell commands to install libraries, set up background services, or access your local file system or network directly, I will provide:\n\n1.  **A complete Python script blueprint**: This will be the `social_poster.py` file.\n2.  **Data structure examples**: For `hik_data.json` and `myanpoh_data.json`.\n3.  **Configuration instructions**: How to set up API keys and tokens.\n4.  **Required Python libraries**: A `requirements.txt` file.\n5.  **Step-by-step Ubuntu installation and execution guide**: How to set up your environment and run the script.\n\n---\n\n### **1. Required Python Libraries (`requirements.txt`)**\n\nCreate a file named `requirements.txt` with the following content:\n\n```\nopenai\npython-telegram-bot\napscheduler\npython-dotenv\ndateparser\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. Configuration (`.env` file)**\n\nCreate a file named `.env` in the same directory as your Python script. Replace placeholder values with your actual keys and tokens.\n\n```dotenv\n# OpenAI API Configuration\nOPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here\n\n# Telegram Bot Configuration\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_telegram_chat_id_here # This is your personal chat ID, not a group ID usually\n\n# Data file paths\nHI_K_DATA_PATH=data/hik_data.json\nMYAN_POH_DATA_PATH=data/myanpoh_data.json\n```\n\n*   **How to get `OPENAI_API_KEY`**: Sign up on the OpenAI platform.\n*   **How to get `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`**:\n    1.  Talk to the `@BotFather` on Telegram.\n    2.  Send `/newbot` and follow its instructions.\n    3.  It will give you an API token.\n*   **How to get `TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID`**:\n    1.  Talk to the `@userinfobot` on Telegram.\n    2.  It will show you your user ID, which is your chat ID for direct messages.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Data Files (`data/` directory)**\n\nCreate a directory named `data` and place the following JSON files inside it.\n\n**`data/hik_data.json`**:\n```json\n{\n  \"business_name\": \"Hi-K\",\n  \"description\": \"Your go-to for authentic Korean cosmetics, K-Pop merchandise, and trending Korean brands. We offer direct sourcing from Korea to Myanmar.\",\n  \"tone\": \"Friendly & Trendy\",\n  \"target_audience\": \"Young people interested in Korean trends, beauty enthusiasts, K-pop fans.\",\n  \"language\": \"Burmese\",\n  \"services\": [\n    \"Direct sourcing from Korea\",\n    \"Cosmetics, K-Pop Merch, Brand items\",\n    \"Personal Shopper service for various items\",\n    \"Service fee: 5-7% supplier fee\",\n    \"Delivery: Express Air Cargo (approx. 2 weeks to Myanmar)\"\n  ],\n  \"examples\": {\n    \"caption_keywords\": [\"K-Beauty\", \"Glow Up\", \"Idol Goods\", \"Trend Alert\", \"Must Have\"],\n    \"cta_keywords\": [\"Inbox\", \"Order Now\", \"Shop Now\", \"DM us\"],\n    \"hashtags\": [\"#HiK\", \"#KoreanBeauty\", \"#KpopMerch\", \"#KoreaTrend\", \"#CosmeticsMyanmar\"]\n  },\n  \"contact_info\": {\n    \"telegram_viber\": \"+82 10-5617-9120\",\n    \"messenger_link\": \"your_hik_messenger_link_here\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**`data/myanpoh_data.json`**:\n```json\n{\n  \"business_name\": \"Myan-Poh Cargo\",\n  \"description\": \"Reliable Korea-Myanmar cargo and logistics service. We handle shipping for individuals, online shops, and businesses.\",\n  \"tone\": \"Professional & Reliable\",\n  \"target_audience\": \"Myanmar citizens in Korea, Myanmar customers wanting to order Korean items, Online shop owners in Myanmar.\",\n  \"language\": \"Burmese\",\n  \"services\": [\n    \"Korea-Myanmar round-trip cargo service\",\n    \"Logistics & Freight forwarding\",\n    \"Personal shopping assistance from Korea\",\n    \"Timely and secure delivery\"\n  ],\n  \"examples\": {\n    \"caption_keywords\": [\"Express Delivery\", \"Cargo Service\", \"Logistics Myanmar\", \"Online Shopping Myanmar\", \"Shipping Service\"],\n    \"cta_keywords\": [\"Contact us\", \"Inquire Now\", \"Get a Quote\"],\n    \"hashtags\": [\"#MyanPohCargo\", \"#KoreaMyanmarCargo\", \"#LogisticsMyanmar\", \"#ShippingService\", \"#MyanmarToKorea\"]\n  },\n  \"contact_info\": {\n    \"phone\": \"+1234567890\",\n    \"messenger_link\": \"your_myanpoh_messenger_link_here\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **4. Python Script (`social_poster.py`)**\n\nSave the following code as `social_poster.py`.\n\n```python\nimport os\nimport json\nimport logging\nimport datetime\nimport dateparser\nfrom dotenv import load_dotenv\nfrom telegram import Update, InlineKeyboardButton, InlineKeyboardMarkup\nfrom telegram.ext import Application, CommandHandler, ContextTypes, MessageHandler, filters, CallbackQueryHandler\n\nfrom openai import OpenAI\nfrom apscheduler.schedulers.asyncio import AsyncIOScheduler\nfrom apscheduler.triggers.date import DateTrigger\n\n# --- Configuration Loading ---\nload_dotenv()\n\nOPENAI_API_KEY = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\") # Your personal chat ID\n\nHI_K_DATA_PATH = os.getenv(\"HI_K_DATA_PATH\", \"data/hik_data.json\")\nMYAN_POH_DATA_PATH = os.getenv(\"MYAN_POH_DATA_PATH\", \"data/myanpoh_data.json\")\n\nif not all([OPENAI_API_KEY, TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID]):\n    raise ValueError(\"Missing required environment variables. Please set OPENAI_API_KEY, TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, and TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID.\")\n\n# Setup logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    level=logging.INFO\n)\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n# --- Data Loading ---\ndef load_business_data(business_name_lower):\n    data_path = None\n    if \"hi-k\" in business_name_lower:\n        data_path = HI_K_DATA_PATH\n    elif \"myan-poh\" in business_name_lower:\n        data_path = MYAN_POH_DATA_PATH\n    else:\n        return None, f\"Business data not found for '{business_name_lower}'. Supported: Hi-K, Myan-Poh.\"\n\n    try:\n        with open(data_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            return json.load(f), None\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        return None, f\"Data file not found at {data_path}.\"\n    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n        return None, f\"Error decoding JSON from {data_path}.\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return None, f\"An unexpected error occurred while loading data: {e}\"\n\n# --- OpenAI Integration ---\nclient = OpenAI(api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY)\n\ndef generate_burmese_caption_and_dalle_prompt(business_data, topic):\n    business_name = business_data.get(\"business_name\", \"Unknown Business\")\n    tone = business_data.get(\"tone\", \"Friendly & Trendy\")\n    audience = business_data.get(\"target_audience\", \"general audience\")\n    services_desc = \", \".join(business_data.get(\"services\", [\"various services\"]))\n    examples = business_data.get(\"examples\", {})\n    cta_keywords = examples.get(\"cta_keywords\", [\"DM us\", \"Contact us\"])\n    topic_hint = f\"related to '{topic}'\" if topic else \"general promotion\"\n\n    # Prompt for Burmese caption\n    caption_prompt = f\"\"\"\nYou are a social media content creator for '{business_name}'.\nYour goal is to create a short, engaging, and trendy Facebook post caption in Burmese.\nThe brand's tone is: {tone}.\nThe target audience is: {audience}.\nKey services/products: {services_desc}.\nThe post topic is: {topic_hint}.\n\nBased on this information, generate a concise Facebook post caption (max 4 sentences) in Burmese.\nInclude a clear Call-to-Action (CTA) using one of these keywords: {', '.join(cta_keywords)}.\nAdd 3-5 relevant hashtags in Burmese and English.\nEnsure the tone is engaging and appropriate for social media.\n\nOutput format:\nCaption: [Your Burmese caption here]\nCTA: [Your chosen CTA here]\nHashtags: #[hashtag1] #[hashtag2] #[hashtag3] #[hashtag4] #[hashtag5]\n\"\"\"\n\n    # Prompt for DALL-E image prompt\n    image_prompt_meta = f\"\"\"\nGenerate a detailed English prompt for DALL-E to create a promotional image for '{business_name}'.\nBrand description: {business_data.get('description', 'N/A')}.\nTone: {tone}.\nTarget Audience: {audience}.\nKey services/products: {services_desc}.\nPost topic: {topic_hint}.\nImage Style Requirements:\n- Lighting: Bright, natural, sometimes with subtle professional studio lighting.\n- Style: Professional, clean, minimalist, modern, with a touch of K-beauty aesthetic or reliability (depending on business).\n- Composition: Focus on showcasing the products/services effectively.\n- Elements to include: [Specify key elements here - e.g., for Hi-K, mention specific cosmetic products or K-pop merch in a flat lay; for Myan-Poh, mention delivery boxes, maps, Korean/Myanmar elements].\n- Output: A square image (1080x1080px) or a format suitable for social media.\n- Use of background: Clean white or light pastel, possibly with a bold accent color (e.g., hot pink, neon teal for Hi-K; subtle blue/white for Myan-Poh) as per previous discussions.\n- Additional notes: Include space for a QR code/social media handle and a tagline.\n\nGenerate the DALL-E prompt based on these specifications. Be descriptive.\n\nImage Prompt:\n\"\"\"\n\n    try:\n        # Generate Burmese Caption and Hashtags\n        caption_response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", # Or another suitable model like gpt-3.5-turbo\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a skilled translator and social media copywriter specializing in Burmese.\"},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": caption_prompt}\n            ],\n            temperature=0.7,\n        )\n        caption_text = caption_response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n\n        # Generate DALL-E Prompt\n        image_prompt_response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o-mini\", # Or another suitable model\n            messages=[\n                {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are an expert AI image prompt engineer.\"},\n                {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": image_prompt_meta}\n            ],\n            temperature=0.8,\n        )\n        dalle_prompt_text = image_prompt_response.choices[0].message.content.strip()\n\n        return caption_text, dalle_prompt_text, None\n    \n    except Exception as e:\n        logger.error(f\"Error generating content with OpenAI: {e}\")\n        return None, None, f\"Error generating content: {e}\"\n\n# --- Telegram Bot Logic ---\nclass SocialPosterBot:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.application = Application.builder().token(TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN).build()\n        self.scheduler = AsyncIOScheduler()\n        self.scheduler.start()\n\n        # Define state for user interaction\n        self.user_state = {} # {chat_id: {'stage': 'awaiting_input'/'awaiting_approval'/'awaiting_time', 'data': {...}}}\n\n        # Register handlers\n        self.application.add_handler(CommandHandler(\"start\", self.start))\n        self.application.add_handler(MessageHandler(filters.TEXT & ~filters.COMMAND, self.handle_message))\n        self.application.add_handler(CallbackQueryHandler(self.handle_button_press))\n\n        self.current_post_data = {} # To store data for the current post being drafted\n\n    async def start(self, update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n        await update.message.reply_text(\"Hello! I'm your Social Poster Bot. Send me a Facebook post request like: 'Draft a Facebook post for Hi-K about new skincare arrivals.'\")\n        self.user_state[update.effective_chat_id] = {'stage': 'awaiting_input'}\n\n    async def handle_message(self, update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n        chat_id = update.effective_chat_id\n        message_text = update.message.text.strip()\n        logger.info(f\"Received message: '{message_text}' from chat_id: {chat_id}\")\n\n        if chat_id not in self.user_state:\n            self.user_state[chat_id] = {'stage': 'awaiting_input'}\n\n        current_stage = self.user_state[chat_id]['stage']\n\n        if current_stage == 'awaiting"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":24139,"output":4907,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29046,"cost":{"input":-24139,"output":-4907,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-29046}},"stopReason":"length","timestamp":1774440978314}}
